thread.title_full: Christie: Trump made me order meatloaf at White House dinner | Washington Examiner

author: Caitlin Yilek
title: Christie: made me order meatloaf at White House dinner
text:
Chris Christie says President Trump made him order meatloaf when the New Jersey governor and his wife, Mary Pat, had dinner at the White House on Tuesday.
Trump told his dinner guests that they could order whatever they wanted off the menu, then said he and Christie would be eating the meatloaf.
''This is what it's like to be with Trump,'' Christie said on a New York sports talk radio show Thursday, the Boston Globe reported . ''He says, 'There's the menu, you guys order whatever you want.' And then he says, 'Chris, you and I are going to have the meatloaf.'''
Trump told Christie "the meatloaf is fabulous."
